@Node quick "SnapShot Manual"
@Next "shotcopyright"
@Prev "reminder"
@Toc "Main"
A QUICK INTRODUCTION TO SNAPSHOT FOR THE BUSY SYSOP


                  1. Add the following to your user-startup:
                              Run <nil: >nil: [Path to reminder:]Reminder


                  2. Create an image of your diskstructure. Open a shell
                     and type:
                              SnapShot DH0: update -a

                  3. Then reboot.


                  4. Bring up the "Reminder" input screen by pressing: 

                               CTRL-ALT-I


                    NOW WE TELL "REMINDER" TO RUN SNAPSHOT EVERY HOUR, ALL
                    DAYS OF THE WEEK:
                    ....................................................

                    From: ??:?? ??/??-???? 
                    To: ??:?? ??/??-???? 
                    Pattern: ??:00 ??/??-????
                    Daycount: 24    
                    Total Count: ??         
                    Weekday: MTWTFSS

                    Message:
                    Command: SnapShot DH0: 0 -a

                    ....................................................


                    (For  further  instructions,  read  the  manual of the
                    Reminder program.  Remember to perform step two, every
                    time, you alter the ROOT, Startup-sequence, C or DEVS.


@Endnode


